text: <@U0UHG4VP1> we'd like integrate CI for our project, where can I find some instructions?
<@U0UHG4VP1|ry> has joined the channel

<@U12452RAP> this is the repo to look at: <https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/gitweb?p=ci-management.git;a=summary> you can clone from here: <https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/#/admin/projects/ci-management>
take a look here for instance: <https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/gitweb?p=ci-management.git;a=tree;f=jjb/fabric-api;h=b86635f9b9ac50237d64282906d14d5934294fa4;hb=HEAD>
more complex examples here: <https://gerrit.hyperledger.org/r/gitweb?p=ci-management.git;a=tree;f=jjb/fabric;h=ea7e968cf7c3b91cc451d70995044ef0e5cfc214;hb=HEAD>
<@U11HH3P7Y> knows quite a bit as well
thanks
<@U0UHG4VP1> can I create new labels in JIRA?
I don't see where can I do that
what labels do you need?
pythonSDK
<https://jira.hyperledger.org/secure/RapidBoard.jspa?rapidView=83>
I create a board and create some stories, we love everyone here to help us.
And it’s better if we got a notification at this channel when anyone submit a patch to the project. Thanks! <@U0UHG4VP1>
<@U12452RAP>: is this a new project like STL or FAB or a label for the FAB project?
<@U0UHG4VP1> i am not quite sure, it is indeed a separate repo in gerrit.
maybe <@U0Z41KY5V> could answer
<@U0UHG4VP1>, it’s about the fabric-sdk-py project, we want to setup a FAB board at the jira, to tracking project related issues and discussions. Thanks!
<@U0Z41KY5V> so if I understand correctly: you want a new project to track your issues directly, you do not want to use the FAB project?
I just want to be sure before I create a project that you want it :slightly_smiling_face:

yes, we fount there’s already a nodeSDK dashboard: <https://jira.hyperledger.org/secure/RapidBoard.jspa?rapidView=41>. Something similar should be good for us, like a pythonSDK. Thanks! <@U0UHG4VP1> <@U12452RAP>
The nodeSDK seems still under FAB? but all related issues can be managed at one place.
Yes I see
